select count(*) as aggregate from (select sales.id as "salesId",
concat(customers.first_name," ",customers.last_name) as "customer",
concat(rep.first_name," ",rep.last_name) as "rep",
rep.document as "documentRep",
customers.document as "document",
customers.id as "cusId",
sales.total as "total",
DATE_FORMAT(sales.emission_date,"%d-%m-%Y") as "date",
DATE_FORMAT(sales.created_at,"%d-%m-%Y") as "beginDate",

DATE_FORMAT(vinculation_form.updated_at,"%d-%m-%Y") as "updateDate",
status.name as "status",
vinculation_form.url as "vinculation_form",
agencies.channel_id as "agencies",
status.id as "status_id",
status.name as "statuSal",
sales.poliza as "poliza",
products.ramoid as "proRamoid",
products.name as "proName",
products.ramodes as "proSegment",
sales_movements.name as "movName",
sales.number_insurance_policy as "numPolicy",
sales.has_been_renewed as "hasRenew",
charges.id as "chargesId",
agent_ss.agentedes as "agentedes",
channels.canalnegodes as "canalnegodes",
IF(sales.allow_cancel_date is not null, IF(NOW()<=sales.allow_cancel_date, "NO", "YES"),"NO") as "allow_cancel" from `sales` left join `customers` on `customers`.`id` = `sales`.`customer_id` left join `vinculation_form` on `sales`.`id` = `vinculation_form`.`sales_id` left join `status` on `status`.`id` = `sales`.`status_id` left join `status` as `status2` on `status2`.`id` = `vinculation_form`.`status_id` left join `users` on `users`.`id` = `sales`.`user_id` left join `agencies` on `agencies`.`id` = `sales`.`agen_id` left join `products_channel` on `products_channel`.`id` = `sales`.`pbc_id` left join `agent_ss` on `agent_ss`.`id` = `products_channel`.`agent_ss` left join `channels` on `channels`.`id` = `agencies`.`channel_id` left join `products` on `products`.`id` = `products_channel`.`product_id` left join `sales_movements` on `sales_movements`.`id` = `sales`.`sales_movements_id` left join `charges` on `charges`.`sales_id` = `sales`.`id` left join `customer_legal_representative` as `rep` on `rep`.`id` = `vinculation_form`.`customer_legal_representative_id` where `sales`.`sales_type_id` in (7) group by `sales`.`id`) as `aggregate_table`
